# UI/UX Clarity

Every screen must answer: **Where am I? What can I do? What happens next?**

## Navigation

- **Desktop (`lg+`)**: persistent sidebar for admin and student; never hide primary nav on scroll
- **Mobile (`< lg`)**: full-width content; primary nav in Sheet drawer via menu button (see `mobile-responsive.mdc`)
- **Sticky `AppTopHeader`** on all breakpoints: breadcrumbs for wayfinding; menu button on mobile only
- Dynamic breadcrumb labels via `SetBreadcrumbs` in nested layouts (level name, group title)
- One clear page title per view (`PageHeader` with accent border); subtitle only when it adds context
- Back links only inside multi-step flows (quiz completion); prefer breadcrumbs for page-level navigation
- Active nav state must be visible (`NavLink` active indicator with left accent bar)

## Visual hierarchy

- One primary action per section (filled button); secondary actions use `outline` or `ghost`
- Group related controls; separate destructive actions (Delete) visually
- Status badges: use consistent variants (`notStarted` → outline, `inProgress` → secondary, `completed` → default)
- Show progress (bars, percent, points) before action buttons on learning flows

## Copy & labels

- All user-facing text via `src/lib/labels.ts` — **English only** (see `english-only.mdc`)
- Buttons use verbs: "Start Learning", "Save Material", not vague "OK" or "Submit" alone
- Empty states explain what to do next, not just "No data"
- Errors state what failed and how to retry

## Avoid confusion

- Do not repeat the same information (title + subtitle saying the same thing)
- Do not add more than one competing primary CTA per card
- Loading: show spinner or skeleton; disabled buttons during async actions
- Theme toggle must stay visible in sidebar footer (Light / Dark / System)

